09/07/2008
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonian President Branko Crvenkovski met on Tuesday (July 8th) with Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski to discuss Skopje's position in talks on the name dispute with Athens. 
Also present were Foreign Minister Antonio Milososki, cabinet chief Martin Protoger and Macedonia's representative in the talks, Nikola Dimitrov. 
Nobody gave a statement after the meeting, which lasted about two hours.
Meanwhile, Greek and Macedonian media reported Tuesday the UN mediator in the dispute, Matthew Nimetz, will hold separate meetings in New York with the representatives of Greece and Macedonia. 
He will reportedly meet the Macedonian side on Friday and Greece's envoy on Monday. 
(Utrinski Vesnik - 09/07/08; Kathimerini, ANA-MPA, MIA, Telma, A1 - 08/07/08)
